<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="79">This species can be readily recognized by having two unique characteristics: the gonostylar apex bare, and a dorsally located lobe on its inflated gonostylus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="79" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="79">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="79">This species is named after its type locality, Shennongjia at Hubei province, China.</paragraph>
